      <h2>Establish fast track delivery for your&nbsp;application&nbsp;</h2>

      <p>
        Imagine you plan to build a new application or add more features to the
        existing one. At the same time, make it more scalable, secure, and
        ensure it is compliant to all corporate or industry regulations. You
        have a great development team or only an intention to create one. But
        most importantly, you do have a clear list of requirements:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Efficient and productive team</strong>.</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Quicker go-to-market for your business features</strong>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong
            >More time for brainstorming&nbsp;on&nbsp;new killer-features
            and&nbsp;hypothesis testing</strong
          >.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong
            >Fewer bugs in the production and readiness to go live at any time
            the business wants it</strong
          >.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        The best way to achieve this is by integrating DevOps practices and
        automation into your processes.<br /><br />DevOps is not only an
        approach to software delivery but also a new management culture that
        embraces Agile software development and uses rapid iterations and
        continuous improvement to achieve business goals faster without
        compromising the quality of service. By automating software development
        routine, it reduces the time and effort spent on manual tasks such as
        application testing, build&nbsp;and deployment. So, itâ€™s a great way to
        make your development team more efficient and allow them to deliver
        faster.
      </p>

                  <div class="editor-content">
                    <p>
                      Taking the security into account from the very beginning
                      not only reduces the total cost of software development
                      but also saves time and reputation. A research shows that
                      discovering a security vulnerability when your product is
                      already in production is almost 100 times more expensive
                      than finding during the development!
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      The question of security is especially important for
                      industries like Fintech or Healthcare where strict
                      compliance policies need to be followed, and having
                      security breaches is an extremely risky and expensive gap.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      By opting for secure development, you are solving not one
                      but a couple of your problems, such as:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Minimize the costs of security-related issues.</li>
                      <li>
                        Avoid repetitive security issues and inconsistent level
                        of security.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Deliver secure source code, secure deployment, secure
                        infrastructure.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Get an application that fully meets compliance (ie.
                        HIPPA, PCI, SOC, PII).
                      </li>
                      <li>Increase trust for key stakeholder and clients.</li>
                    </ul>
